// Editor self-visibility regression. When the analyzer opens a device's always-merged impl file, it
// reconstructs the WHOLE device (datasheet + the SELECTED variant), treating those files as the SAME
// unit as the open file — so BOTH resolve here:
//   - `handle`   : a type from the sibling datasheet (selfvis.ds.arche), and
//   - `sv_make`  : a `#module`-PRIVATE `#foreign` in the selected x11 variant (x11/impl.arche).
// In a full build these are one unit, so the editor must agree (no false "undefined"/"unknown type").
//
// RUN: ! env ARCHE_SELECT=selfvis=x11 %analyzer --dump %s 2>&1 | grep "Undefined symbol 'sv_make'"
// RUN: ! env ARCHE_SELECT=selfvis=x11 %analyzer --dump %s 2>&1 | grep "unknown type 'handle'"
make :: proc()(h: handle) {
  sv_make()(h);
}
